{"id":15,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":15,"title":"Chapter 12: King Benjamin","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 12"],["h1","King Benjamin"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p3"},"King Benjamin was a righteous Nephite king. With the help of other righteous men, he brought peace to the land."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/w-of-m/1.17-18"},"Words of Mormon 1:17–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p5"},"King Benjamin became old and wanted to talk to his people. He needed to tell them that his son Mosiah would be the next king."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/1.9-10"},"Mosiah 1:9–10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p7"},"The people came from all over the land and gathered near the temple. They placed their tents so the doors faced the temple."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/2.1,5-6"},"Mosiah 2:1, 5–6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p9"},"King Benjamin spoke from a tower so the Nephites could hear him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/2.7"},"Mosiah 2:7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p11"},"He told his people that he had tried hard to serve them. He said the way to serve God is by serving one another."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/2.14,17"},"Mosiah 2:14, 17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p13"},"King Benjamin told the people to obey God’s commandments. Those who faithfully keep the commandments will be happy and someday live with God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/2.41"},"Mosiah 2:41"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p15"},"King Benjamin said Jesus Christ would soon be born on the earth. His mother’s name would be Mary."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.5,8"},"Mosiah 3:5, 8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p17"},"Jesus would perform miracles. He would heal the sick and bring the dead back to life. He would make the blind see and the deaf hear."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.5"},"Mosiah 3:5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p19"},"Jesus would suffer and die for the sins of all people. Those who repent and have faith in Jesus will be forgiven of their sins."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.7,11-12"},"Mosiah 3:7, 11–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p21"},"King Benjamin told the Nephites that wicked men would whip Jesus. Then they would crucify him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.9"},"Mosiah 3:9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p23"},"After three days Jesus would be resurrected."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.10"},"Mosiah 3:10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p25"},"After King Benjamin spoke, the Nephites fell to the ground. They were sorry for their sins and wanted to repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.1-2"},"Mosiah 4:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p27"},"The people had faith in Jesus Christ, and they prayed to be forgiven."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.2"},"Mosiah 4:2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p29"},"The Holy Ghost filled their hearts. They knew that God had forgiven them and that he loved them. They felt peace and joy."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.3"},"Mosiah 4:3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p31"},"King Benjamin told his people to believe in God. He wanted them to know that God had created all things and that he is wise and powerful."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.9"},"Mosiah 4:9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p33"},"King Benjamin told the people to be humble and pray every day. He wanted his people to always remember God and be faithful."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.10-11"},"Mosiah 4:10–11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p35"},"He told the parents not to let their children fight or argue."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.14"},"Mosiah 4:14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_18.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p37","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p37"},"He told them to teach their children to be obedient and to love and serve one another."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p38","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p38"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.15"},"Mosiah 4:15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f19"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_19.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p39","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p39"},"He warned the people to be careful with what they thought, said, and did. They were to be faithful and keep the commandments for the rest of their lives."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p40"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.30"},"Mosiah 4:30"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f20"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_20.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p41"},"King Benjamin asked the people if they believed his teachings. They all said they did. The Holy Ghost had changed them, and they no longer wanted to sin."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p42","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p42"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/5.1-2"},"Mosiah 5:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f21"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_21.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p43","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p43"},"They all covenanted, or promised, to keep God’s commandments. King Benjamin was pleased."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p44","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p44"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/5.5-6"},"Mosiah 5:5–6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_22.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p45","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p45"},"King Benjamin gave his son Mosiah the right to be the new king. Three years later King Benjamin died."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p46","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p46"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/6.3,5"},"Mosiah 6:3, 5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.f23"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_015_23.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p47"},"Mosiah was a righteous king. He worked hard and served his people, as his father had."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p48","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-12-king-benjamin.p48"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/6.6-7"},"Mosiah 6:6–7"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
